[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_j4675")
reagent_id = "C"
title = "Carbon"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Symbol:[/cell][cell]C[/cell]
[cell]Element:[/cell][cell]Carbon[/cell]
[cell]Atomic number:[/cell][cell]6[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]12 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Important properties[/b]
• A non-metal element.
• The basis of organic chemistry and life on Earth.
• Exists in different forms called allotropes (for example diamond and graphite).
[b]Where carbon is found[/b]
• In living organisms.
• In coal, oil, and natural gas.
• In the atmosphere as carbon dioxide (CO₂).
[b]Uses[/b]
• Graphite is used in pencils and electrodes.
• Diamond is used in jewelry and cutting tools.
• Important for making fuels, plastics, and many chemicals.
[b]Safety[/b]
Carbon itself is generally safe, but some carbon compounds (like carbon monoxide, CO) are very toxic."
